div.p: Hiawatha will be joining in the #LightsForTheFight tonight (4/17) to show support for the Class of 2020, as well as healthcare workers, first responders, and all other essential workers on the frontlines of this pandemic. Hiawatha's football field stadium lights and scoreboard will be lit from 8:00pm-8:30pm.

The stadium will be closed to practice social distancing, but please feel free to drive by on Hortense St or do a loop through the bus barn parking lot. We will post pictures and a video of the stadium afterwards.
